l life. Brandes demonstrates how recovering alcoholics in Mexico redefine gender roles in order to preserve masculine identity. He also explains how an organization rooted historically in evangelical Protestantism has been able to flourish in Roman Catholic Latin America.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aAlcoholicsxRehabilitationzMexicozMexico City. 0aRecovering alcoholicszMexicozMexico City. 0aTwelve-step programszMexicozMexico CityxSociological aspects. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292796515423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292796515/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK